          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For the 2- to 8-MeV deuteron energy range pieces of",
                "1.4-mil rolled beryllium foil were used as a target.",
                "This foil was sandwiched between five 4-mil",
                "thicknesses of aluminum backing and another of aluminum",
                "foils which was used to slow the beam to the desired",
                "energy. This sandwich was then covered by a 'hut' of",
                "three 4-mil thicknesses of aluminum foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USACHI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 37-inch 8-Mev cyclotron and"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CCW"
                ],
                "institute": "1USACHI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the 400-kev Cockroft-Walton accelerator",
                "supplied the deuterons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GEMUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Self-quenching G-M counters containing argon,",
                "alcohol, and up to two centimeters of hydrogen have",
                "been used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "After a bombardment was completed, the beryllium and",
                "all the aluminum foils were placed in a alumina cup in",
                "porcelain furnace tube in a hydrogen atmosphere. This",
                "tube was heated for thirty minutes to 950 to 1000",
                "degr. After cooling to about 350 degr., the hydrogen,",
                "now containing the tritium, was pumped into a counter",
                "already containing 1.8 cm ethylene and 6 cm argon and",
                "was counted."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  Counting errors and local variations in",
                "thickness of the thin berryllium foils contributed to",
                "the errors in the individual mean cross-section",
                "determination."
              ]
            }
          ],
